-- National Bank of Oman picks banks for potential bond sale 
-- By Archana Narayanan
-- Mon Sep 22, 2014 05:52AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, Sept 22 (Reuters) - National Bank of Oman <NBO.OM>, the sultanate's second-largest lender by assets, has picked four banks for a potential U.S. dollar-denominated benchmark bond issue, a document from arranging banks said on Monday.

The bank has mandated Credit Agricole <CAGR.PA>, HSBC <HSBC.L>, National Bank of Abu Dhabi <NBAD.AD>, and Standard Chartered <STAN.L> to arrange investor meetings in the Middle East, Europe and Asia starting on September 25.  A Reg S only bond offering may follow subject to market conditions, the source said. National Bank of Oman is rated BBB plus by Fitch and A3 by Moody's.